1254
00:46:31.288 --> 00:46:33.891
And any time we see
parted hair down the middle.

1255
00:46:33.991 --> 00:46:35.292
it's Cher for us.

1256
00:46:35.392 --> 00:46:37.161
It just was confusing.

1257
00:46:37.261 --> 00:46:39.263
- Yeah. there's so many
mixed messages here.

1258
00:46:39.363 --> 00:46:43.000
It just does not read as goth.

1259
00:46:43.100 --> 00:46:44.468
Walk me through your thinking.

1260
00:46:44.568 --> 00:46:47.304
- My first thought was to do
a floor-length trumpet gown.

1261
00:46:47.404 --> 00:46:48.372
Can you imagine?

1262
00:46:48.472 --> 00:46:50.941
And I was talking with Dawn.

1263
00:46:51.041 --> 00:46:54.611
And I got what I interpreted
as really helpful advice.

1264
00:46:54.711 --> 00:46:57.247
which was. this is what
I would expect Plasma to make.

1265
00:46:57.347 --> 00:46:58.916
And so I was thinking.

1266
00:46:59.016 --> 00:47:02.319
I'm just gonna go
in a brand-new direction.

1267
00:47:02.419 --> 00:47:04.121
- Did anyone help you with it?

1268
00:47:04.221 --> 00:47:06.590
- Other than Dawn's...

1269
00:47:06.690 --> 00:47:08.058
- Sabotage?

1270
00:47:08.158 --> 00:47:10.147
- Yeah. other than Dawn's
dagger in my back... ah...

1271
00:47:10.227 --> 00:47:13.797
Then no. I did all this myself.

1272
00:47:13.897 --> 00:47:16.466
[laughter]

1273
00:47:18.435 --> 00:47:19.570
- All right. y'all.

1274
00:47:19.670 --> 00:47:22.039
Break time is over
at the haunted mansion.

1275
00:47:22.139 --> 00:47:23.807
Sapphira.

1276
00:47:23.907 --> 00:47:25.475
- This is beautiful.

1277
00:47:25.576 --> 00:47:26.844
The hem is finished.

1278
00:47:26.944 --> 00:47:28.378
The sleeves are gorgeous.

1279
00:47:28.478 --> 00:47:30.981
You never let us down when
it comes to knowing your body.

1280
00:47:31.081 --> 00:47:32.983
- The construction. incredible.

1281
00:47:33.083 --> 00:47:35.163
There's even a funny. like.
bustle in the back.

1282
00:47:35.252 --> 00:47:36.887
Those details are beyond.

1283
00:47:36.987 --> 00:47:38.622
They're hard to engineer.

1284
00:47:38.722 --> 00:47:40.858
- I love the fact that
you used this fabric.

1285
00:47:40.958 --> 00:47:43.493
which is very unique.
very cracked mirror.

1286
00:47:43.594 --> 00:47:45.262
And it's just off-kilter.

1287
00:47:45.362 --> 00:47:48.332
which really sold
the goth storyline.

1288
00:47:48.432 --> 00:47:50.367
- Not only do
you look beautiful.

1289
00:47:50.467 --> 00:47:52.703
but you made us laugh so hard.

1290
00:47:52.803 --> 00:47:55.138
You committed to your
character the whole time.

1291
00:47:55.239 --> 00:47:56.460
- Yeah. you sold the garment.

1292
00:47:56.540 --> 00:47:57.608
You were very bothered.

1293
00:47:57.708 --> 00:47:59.142
You were dead on your feet.

1294
00:47:59.243 --> 00:48:00.397
- No wonder you were
so bothered.

1295
00:48:00.477 --> 00:48:01.678
You made two garments.

1296
00:48:01.778 --> 00:48:03.480
[laughter]

1297
00:48:03.580 --> 00:48:05.616
- It was a really
funny presentation.

1298
00:48:05.716 --> 00:48:07.171
And I think it took it
over the top.

1299
00:48:07.251 --> 00:48:08.652
- Thank you.

1300
00:48:08.752 --> 00:48:11.955
- Up next. the Nymphia Wind
beneath my wings.

1301
00:48:12.055 --> 00:48:13.790
- You came out.
and it was a production

1302
00:48:13.891 --> 00:48:15.792
of the most beautiful caliber.

1303
00:48:15.893 --> 00:48:17.761
- I love this.

1304
00:48:17.861 --> 00:48:21.164
I think you could walk down
a couture runway today.

1305
00:48:21.265 --> 00:48:24.401
This looks like
Vivienne Westwood bridal.

1306
00:48:24.501 --> 00:48:26.503
And I kind of want to wear it.

1307
00:48:26.603 --> 00:48:29.773
- You are such a genius
with different textures.

1308
00:48:29.873 --> 00:48:32.943
I mean. the ostrich feathers.
and the sparkle in that lace.

1309
00:48:33.043 --> 00:48:34.177
and the draping.

1310
00:48:34.278 --> 00:48:35.799
You're a superstar
when it comes to fashion.

1311
00:48:35.879 --> 00:48:39.516
- It's perfectly styled.
beautiful silhouette.

1312
00:48:39.616 --> 00:48:40.851
I love the fabrics.

1313
00:48:40.951 --> 00:48:42.452
It's just fantastic.

1314
00:48:42.552 --> 00:48:45.188
You've come a long way
from yellow.

1315
00:48:45.289 --> 00:48:46.823
- I have.

1316
00:48:46.924 --> 00:48:49.226
- Now. did you go
to fashion school?

1317
00:48:49.326 --> 00:48:50.894
- Yes. I did.
- Where?

1318
00:48:50.994 --> 00:48:54.698
- I went to the UK
to study Fashion Atelier.

1319
00:48:54.798 --> 00:48:56.066
- Well. it shows.

1320
00:48:56.166 --> 00:48:58.802
Beautiful.
- Thank you.

1321
00:48:58.902 --> 00:49:01.071
- Up next. it's Q.

1322
00:49:01.171 --> 00:49:03.807
- I wish I could say
I loved this.

1323
00:49:03.907 --> 00:49:05.175
but that's not even enough.

1324
00:49:05.275 --> 00:49:07.444
It's more than that.
It's everything.

1325
00:49:07.544 --> 00:49:11.715
You went with a light base.
and then you added black roses.

1326
00:49:11.815 --> 00:49:14.751
And it creates
this beautiful haute couture

1327
00:49:14.851 --> 00:49:16.119
scary clown look.

1328
00:49:16.219 --> 00:49:18.155
- It's punk rock meets goth

1329
00:49:18.255 --> 00:49:20.557
with fashion fully taking over.

1330
00:49:20.657 --> 00:49:22.492
- You look like
a beautiful nightmare.

1331
00:49:22.592 --> 00:49:25.095
And I'm so beyond impressed.

1332
00:49:25.195 --> 00:49:27.664
10 out of 10.
absolutely stunning.

1333
00:49:27.764 --> 00:49:28.899
- Thank you.

1334
00:49:28.999 --> 00:49:31.101
- From the silhouette
down to the texture.

1335
00:49:31.201 --> 00:49:35.639
to the construction.
it is exquisite.

1336
00:49:35.739 --> 00:49:38.108
And then the lining.

1337
00:49:38.208 --> 00:49:39.710
Oh my gosh.

1338
00:49:39.810 --> 00:49:41.278
Wow!

1339
00:49:41.378 --> 00:49:43.046
Just beautiful.

1340
00:49:43.146 --> 00:49:44.781
- I don't know.
I'm just honestly

1341
00:49:44.881 --> 00:49:47.017
kind of surprised myself
with this one.

1342
00:49:47.117 --> 00:49:49.753
Every single detail is.
like. hand cut out.

1343
00:49:49.853 --> 00:49:51.688
Just very. very proud
of this piece.

1344
00:49:51.788 --> 00:49:53.824
- Well. thank you.
- Thank you so much.

1345
00:49:53.924 --> 00:49:55.979
- Thank you. queens.
I think we've heard enough.

1346
00:49:56.059 --> 00:49:58.929
While you untuck
in the Lush Lounge.

1347
00:49:59.029 --> 00:50:01.331
the judges and I
will deliberate.

1348
00:50:02.933 --> 00:50:04.935
OK. just between us girlfriends.

1349
00:50:05.035 --> 00:50:06.370
what do you think?

1350
00:50:06.470 --> 00:50:07.704
Plane Jane.

1351
00:50:07.804 --> 00:50:09.826
- She has been a frontrunner
from the beginning.

1352
00:50:09.906 --> 00:50:11.675
working really hard
to stay there.

1353
00:50:11.775 --> 00:50:14.778
But it wasn't up
to the caliber that I expect.

1354
00:50:14.878 --> 00:50:16.079
So for me. it was like. OK.

1355
00:50:16.179 --> 00:50:17.714
- I would love to have seen

1356
00:50:17.814 --> 00:50:19.483
some huge shoulder pads.
you know?

1357
00:50:19.583 --> 00:50:21.952
But listen.
it was still fantastic.

1358
00:50:22.052 --> 00:50:23.020
Mhi'ya.

1359
00:50:23.120 --> 00:50:25.989
- Well. not Mhi'ya
favorite tonight.

1360
00:50:26.089 --> 00:50:26.990
- Almost everyone
felt like they had

1361
00:50:27.090 --> 00:50:28.425
a very distinct point of view.

1362
00:50:28.525 --> 00:50:30.527
I didn't really get that
from Mhi'ya.

1363
00:50:30.627 --> 00:50:32.229
- I don't think
she really understood

1364
00:50:32.329 --> 00:50:33.563
the story she was telling.

1365
00:50:33.663 --> 00:50:34.998
And I think that happens

1366
00:50:35.098 --> 00:50:38.068
when someone helps you do
the project.

1367
00:50:38.168 --> 00:50:39.069
- Dawn.

1368
00:50:39.169 --> 00:50:40.871
- All of it was so cool.

1369
00:50:40.971 --> 00:50:43.040
so beautiful. and so drag.

1370
00:50:43.140 --> 00:50:45.275
- I think Dawn really
understands her brand.

1371
00:50:45.375 --> 00:50:46.530
And she brings it every time.

1372
00:50:46.610 --> 00:50:48.812
She really understood
the Goth assignment.

1373
00:50:48.912 --> 00:50:51.301
And I thought this was one
of the best looks of the night.

1374
00:50:51.381 --> 00:50:52.449
- Morphine.

1375
00:50:52.549 --> 00:50:55.118
- Morphine was
a little sedate for me.

1376
00:50:55.218 --> 00:50:56.620
And...
- I get that.

1377
00:50:56.720 --> 00:50:58.240
- Thank you.
I'm here every Tuesday.

1378
00:50:58.321 --> 00:50:59.956
Try the burger.

1379
00:51:00.057 --> 00:51:01.758
- Not the worst.
certainly not the best.

1380
00:51:01.858 --> 00:51:04.027
But she did look purty.

1381
00:51:04.127 --> 00:51:05.328
- Plasma.

1382
00:51:05.429 --> 00:51:08.565
- I have a soft place
in my heart for Plasma.

1383
00:51:08.665 --> 00:51:10.367
I fell in love with her tonight.

1384
00:51:10.467 --> 00:51:12.636
- But I don't even know
what her point of view was.

1385
00:51:12.736 --> 00:51:13.937
I don't get it. You

1386
00:51:14.037 --> 00:51:15.672
can't just give yourself
a blue-black lip

1387
00:51:15.772 --> 00:51:16.673
and say. I'm goth.

1388
00:51:16.773 --> 00:51:18.275
- [laughs]

1389
00:51:18.375 --> 00:51:20.010
- You gotta try!

1390
00:51:20.110 --> 00:51:21.711
- But she owned it.

1391
00:51:21.812 --> 00:51:24.414
And I think that I have
respect for that.

1392
00:51:24.514 --> 00:51:26.403
- Yeah. you gotta respect the
way she walked out on stage.

1393
00:51:26.483 --> 00:51:29.319
She's just like. bitches.
I'm letting you have it.

1394
00:51:29.419 --> 00:51:30.454
- Yes!

1395
00:51:30.554 --> 00:51:32.122
- Let's talk about Sapphira.

1396
00:51:32.222 --> 00:51:34.658
- We all know what Sapphira
can do at this point.

1397
00:51:34.758 --> 00:51:38.195
She came out. like she always
does. telling a story.

1398
00:51:38.295 --> 00:51:40.117
- I just was laughing
and having so much fun.

1399
00:51:40.197 --> 00:51:41.918
And that's what you want
when you're watching drag.

1400
00:51:41.998 --> 00:51:43.834
- It wasn't
the most over-the-top.

1401
00:51:43.934 --> 00:51:45.702
but it was really well done.

1402
00:51:45.802 --> 00:51:48.138
- She gave us goth.
but in her way.

1403
00:51:48.238 --> 00:51:49.272
- Nymphia.

1404
00:51:49.372 --> 00:51:50.527
- Nymphia knows
how to turn a look.

1405
00:51:50.607 --> 00:51:52.029
She's been doing it
since day one.

1406
00:51:52.109 --> 00:51:54.911
My only complaint was that
we couldn't see her face.

1407
00:51:55.011 --> 00:51:57.167
- I don't know. I've walked
a Mark Jacobs runway or two

1408
00:51:57.247 --> 00:51:58.527
where you could not see my face.

1409
00:51:58.615 --> 00:52:00.737
And it doesn't matter because
the clothes are so good.

1410
00:52:00.817 --> 00:52:03.520
So I really appreciated
this look.

1411
00:52:03.620 --> 00:52:06.590
I mean. I just could see this
on the runway tomorrow.

1412
00:52:06.690 --> 00:52:07.791
- Q.

1413
00:52:07.891 --> 00:52:09.559
- She didn't understand
the assignment.

1414
00:52:09.659 --> 00:52:12.429
She redefined the assignment.

1415
00:52:12.529 --> 00:52:14.431
- So brilliant.
It was couture.

1416
00:52:14.531 --> 00:52:16.386
- And now there's
a worldwide taffeta shortage.

1417
00:52:16.466 --> 00:52:18.602
- [laughs]
- Thank you very much. Q.

1418
00:52:18.702 --> 00:52:20.490
- That's gonna go down
in the history books.

1419
00:52:20.570 --> 00:52:22.339
that outfit right there.
- Oh. yeah.

1420
00:52:22.439 --> 00:52:25.509
- Silence!
I've made my decision.

1421
00:52:25.609 --> 00:52:29.212
Bring back my girls.

1422
00:52:29.312 --> 00:52:30.981
Welcome back. queens.

1423
00:52:31.081 --> 00:52:32.482
I've made some decisions.

1424
00:52:32.582 --> 00:52:35.452
[dramatic music]

1425
00:52:35.552 --> 00:52:39.489
Q. tonight. the ghost
of fashion past.

1426
00:52:39.589 --> 00:52:42.292
present. and future salutes you.

1427
00:52:44.227 --> 00:52:46.296
Condragulations.
you are the winner

1428
00:52:46.396 --> 00:52:47.998
of this week's challenge.

1429
00:52:48.098 --> 00:52:49.766
[applause]

1430
00:52:49.866 --> 00:52:51.701
- Thank you.
Thank you so much.

1431
00:52:51.801 --> 00:52:54.638
- You've won a cash prize
of $5.000.

1432
00:52:54.738 --> 00:52:58.408
presented by got2b Color Remix.

1433
00:52:58.508 --> 00:53:00.377
You may step to the back
of the stage.

1434
00:53:00.477 --> 00:53:01.845
- Thank you.

1435
00:53:01.945 --> 00:53:03.780
I'm so thrilled.

1436
00:53:03.880 --> 00:53:07.551
If I didn't get this win.
I was gonna be cracked.

1437
00:53:07.651 --> 00:53:10.453
Second time.
second design challenge win.

1438
00:53:10.554 --> 00:53:12.289
I should have honestly
gotten all three

1439
00:53:12.389 --> 00:53:14.958
design challenge wins.
[laughs]

1440
00:53:16.493 --> 00:53:18.628
- Plane Jane.

1441
00:53:18.728 --> 00:53:20.230
Dawn.

1442
00:53:20.330 --> 00:53:21.631
Sapphira.

1443
00:53:21.731 --> 00:53:23.133
Nymphia.

1444
00:53:23.233 --> 00:53:24.734
you are all safe.

1445
00:53:26.169 --> 00:53:27.524
You may step to the back
of the stage.

1446
00:53:27.604 --> 00:53:29.639
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1447
00:53:34.411 --> 00:53:38.748
- Mhi'ya Iman Le'Paige.
you're a beautiful bird.

1448
00:53:38.848 --> 00:53:41.918
but your goth look
didn't take flight.

1449
00:53:43.286 --> 00:53:46.890
Morphine.
your makeup was unspookable.

1450
00:53:46.990 --> 00:53:51.695
but your Morticia look
wasn't Cousin It.

1451
00:53:53.230 --> 00:53:57.400
Plasma. we loved
your runway presentation.

1452
00:53:57.500 --> 00:54:00.070
but your goth look
made us shrug.

1453
00:54:06.076 --> 00:54:08.211
Morphine...

1454
00:54:08.311 --> 00:54:09.212
you are safe.

1455
00:54:09.312 --> 00:54:10.513
- Ooh.

1456
00:54:12.816 --> 00:54:15.085
Thank you.
- You may join the other girls.

1457
00:54:17.320 --> 00:54:18.755
Mhi'ya.

1458
00:54:18.855 --> 00:54:20.156
Plasma.

1459
00:54:20.257 --> 00:54:24.494
I'm sorry. my dears.
but you are up for elimination.

1460
00:54:24.594 --> 00:54:26.863
- It's my third time
lip-synching.

1461
00:54:26.963 --> 00:54:29.132
And I know I have to do more.

1462
00:54:29.232 --> 00:54:30.834
I have to bring more
to the table.

1463
00:54:30.934 --> 00:54:35.105
So if I have to be the lip-sync
assassin of this season.

1464
00:54:35.205 --> 00:54:37.440
give me my mask. and let's go.

1465
00:54:37.540 --> 00:54:40.777
- Two queens stand before me.

1466
00:54:40.877 --> 00:54:44.547
Ladies. this is your
last chance to impress me

1467
00:54:44.648 --> 00:54:47.884
and save yourself
from elimination.

1468
00:54:47.984 --> 00:54:49.986
[dramatic music]

1469
00:54:50.086 --> 00:54:55.558
The time has come for you
to lip-synch

1470
00:54:55.659 --> 00:54:58.762
for your life.

1471
00:55:01.197 --> 00:55:03.366
- This is my first time
in the bottom two.

1472
00:55:03.466 --> 00:55:07.170
After two wins. I've proven
why I should still be here.

1473
00:55:07.270 --> 00:55:10.373
I'm a performer.
so I'm not scared of Mhi'ya.

1474
00:55:10.473 --> 00:55:12.375
I'm not scared of anything.

1475
00:55:12.475 --> 00:55:17.347
- Good luck.
and don't fuck it up.

1476
00:55:17.447 --> 00:55:22.786
[Lady Gaga's "Bloody Mary"]

1477
00:55:22.886 --> 00:55:24.487
- [singing] Love is just

1478
00:55:24.587 --> 00:55:26.389
a history that they may prove.

1479
00:55:26.489 --> 00:55:28.224
And when you're gone.

1480
00:55:28.325 --> 00:55:30.126
I'll tell them
my religion's you.

1481
00:55:30.226 --> 00:55:33.897
When Punktious comes to kill
the king upon his throne.

1482
00:55:33.997 --> 00:55:37.300
I'm ready for their stones.

1483
00:55:37.400 --> 00:55:39.302
I'll dance. dance dance

1484
00:55:39.402 --> 00:55:40.904
with my hands. hands. hands

1485
00:55:41.004 --> 00:55:42.839
above my head. head. head

1486
00:55:42.939 --> 00:55:44.741
like Jesus said.

1487
00:55:44.841 --> 00:55:45.842
- That bitch got petals.

1488
00:55:45.942 --> 00:55:48.278
She is giving us
a Sasha Velour moment!

1489
00:55:48.378 --> 00:55:49.633
- [singing] Hands above my head.

1490
00:55:49.713 --> 00:55:51.915
Hands together.
forgive him before he's dead

1491
00:55:52.015 --> 00:55:54.718
- I've never seen a wig reveal
into a beanie before.

1492
00:55:54.818 --> 00:55:56.606
That's a new one on
"RuPaul's Drag Race." honey.

1493
00:55:56.686 --> 00:55:59.756
- [singing]
Because I won't cry for you.

1494
00:55:59.856 --> 00:56:03.326
I won't crucify
the things you do.

1495
00:56:03.426 --> 00:56:04.828
- Not in a gown. bitch!

1496
00:56:04.928 --> 00:56:06.730
- [singing] I won't cry for you.

1497
00:56:06.830 --> 00:56:08.264
See. when you're gone.

1498
00:56:08.365 --> 00:56:12.569
I'll still be Bloody Mary.

